            <abstract><p>Thanks for Pleasance's letter. Weather "very hot", and he is going on with his "[English] Flora". Asks that Pleasance give "dear little Pleasy some kisses for [him]". Comments on flowers in the garden, including 'Coreopsis tinctroia', 'Agapanthus', and 'Balsam'. His plans for the next few days.</p><p>[Note by Pleasance Smith on recto of second folio] "I think this is my dear James's last letter!".</p></abstract>
